description:
Many people argue that Christians and atheists shouldn’t even discuss faith, they should leave religion out of dialogue because it is exclusive and truth is relative. What holds true for me doesn’t necessarily ring true for someone else, right? So is there no absolute truth? Is everything subjective? Doctor Pandit evaluates the idea of relativism.

Some people also argue that all religions lead to the same end. This religious pluralism is becoming more popular in our modern day, and sometimes this equality of religions sounds appealing. Listen and learn about how we can properly address why every religion claims to be the only way to salvation. How is this incompatible with pluralism? Hear Doctor Pandit reveal the logical and reasonable explanation for why relativism and pluralism is not compatible with truth. 

For more please visit: 
https://amazingdiscoveries.org
